cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically with the problem of wide-baseline matching. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of feature detectors and tentative correspondence selection, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The use of synthesized images and geometry estimation suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.GR (Graphics), while the evaluation of the algorithm's performance on publicly available datasets suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper's focus on matching images from different modalities and with significant lighting changes suggests that it may also belong to cs.RO (Robotics).
